<p>Across all of it, three rules matter most for a Frenchie: <strong>feed highly digestible food in smaller, slower meals</strong> to calm the gut and the gas; <strong>favour a clean named protein and low-allergen recipe</strong> (with omega-3) to settle the skin and folds; and <strong>keep your pup lean</strong>, because a French Bulldog carrying extra weight breathes and cools far worse than one in trim condition. Clean and dry the folds regularly alongside the diet — food is one half of skin health, hygiene the other. Because the breed is genuinely prone to digestive disease, if gas, bloating, soft stools, skin trouble or weight changes noticeably and doesn't settle, book a vet check rather than writing it off as "just a Frenchie thing".</p>

